

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="death + rebirth">
  <Article
    title="death + rebirth"
    section="death"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      rebirth is not a return to what was, but the emergence of something
      different after an ending. it follows death, but does not erase it.
    </p>

    <p>
      what has ended leaves a mark. rebirth carries that mark forward,
      changed by what has been lost.
    </p>

    <p>
      because of this, rebirth is rarely clean. it is shaped by what came
      before it.
    </p>

    <h2>continuity</h2>

    <p>
      rebirth does not begin from nothing. it grows out of what has already
      happened.
    </p>

    <p>
      even when something feels completely new, it is connected to the
      process that led to it.
    </p>

    <h2>difference</h2>

    <p>
      rebirth is not repetition. something shifts. what returns is not
      identical to what was lost.
    </p>

    <p>
      this difference is what allows movement rather than stagnation.
    </p>

    <h2>cycle</h2>

    <p>
      death and rebirth form a cycle rather than a line. endings give
      rise to beginnings, and beginnings move again toward endings.
    </p>

    <p>
      in this way, rebirth does not escape death—it includes it.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death">back to death index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death/dance-of-death">return to: dance of death</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/death/memento-mori">memento mori</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>